<p>John displays drop in unknown items after chapter 4 to around 20-25% per chapter. Keep in mind these numbers include names and hapaxlegomena.</p>

<p>To me this shows that reading through John as a way to teach students Koine Greek is a decent strategy. They will need much more support in the early chapters, but should begin to feel some success in chapters 8-9 and again in 14-17.</p>

<p>Of course this is based on lemmata. What about forms?</p>

<p>The following table shows the number of unknown forms encountered in a given chapter after reading app the preceding chapters. Again it tapers off as did the numbers for the lemmata, but the percentage of unknown items is 20-35% and drops below 40% after chapter 6 rather than chapter 4.</p>

